item.title: Welcome traveler
item.description: I am a Research Assistant for Princeton’s Woodrow Wilson School professor Christopher Neilson. My academic interests lie within the fields of education, industrial organization and econometrics. Interests beyond acedemia include anything computers and music. Prior to this current position I completed a B.A. in Economics at Southern Connecticut State University, graduating in Fall 2016. Throughout my undergraduate degree I worked at a small local company as a business analyst. This website is hosted on GitHub Pages, with its source code in a public GitHub repository.
